<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Reconstruction Finance Corporation was created to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Provide direct aid to individuals</option>
            <option letter="b">Support banks and businesses with loans</option>
            <option letter="c">Fund public works projects</option>
            <option letter="d">Regulate the stock market</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Reconstruction Finance Corporation was created by Hoover in 1932 to provide government loans to banks, railroads, and other businesses. This approach reflected Hoover's belief that helping financial institutions would eventually benefit the general public through a "trickle-down" effect, rather than providing direct aid to individuals suffering during the Depression.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
